	"system": {
		"description": "<p>At 10th level you start to appreciate that the “alive” part of dead or alive takes more effort but usually pays better. Whenever you deal your @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.vKckTQevhrZgeJJ9]{Favored Ordnance} damage to a creature while it is bloodied, it makes a Constitution saving throw against your maneuver DC. On a failed save the creature is knocked [[/condition id=unconscious]] for 1 hour. A creature knocked unconscious in this way can repeat the saving throw when it takes damage or if another adjacent creature uses an action to wake it. Once a creature successfully saves against this feature it is immune to Knockout for the next 24 hours.</p>",
